<inglise> COUNCIL DIRECTIVE 97/61/EC of 20 October 1997 amending the Annex to Directive 91/492/EEC laying down the health conditions for the production and placing on the market of live bivalve molluscs </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU DIREKTIIV 97/61/E&Uuml;, millega muudetakse direktiivi 91/942/EM&Uuml; (milles s&auml;testatakse elusate kahepoolmeliste karploomade tootmise ja turuleviimise tervishoiun&otilde;uded) lisa 20. oktoober 1997 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Directive 91/492/EEC of 15 July 1991 laying down the health conditions for the production and placing on the market of live bivalve molluscs (1), and in particular Article 11 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 15. juuli 1991. aasta direktiivi 91/492/EM&Uuml;, milles s&auml;testatakse elusate kahepoolmeliste karploomade tootmise ja turuleviimise tervishoiun&otilde;uded, (1) eriti selle artiklit 11, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Chapter V of the Annex to Directive 91/492/EEC sets the acceptable limit values for two types of marine toxin that constitute a danger to public health; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: direktiivi 91/492/EM&Uuml; lisa V peat&uuml;kis s&auml;testatakse lubatavad piirnormid kahte liiki merelistele toksiinidele, mis on rahva tervisele ohtlikud; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas there is scientific evidence that a new marine toxin 'Amnesic Shellfish Poisoning' (ASP) that could endanger consumer health has appeared in the areas where bivalve molluscs are produced; </inglise>
<eesti> on teaduslikke t&otilde;endusmaterjale selle kohta, et aladel, kus elusaid kahepoolmelisi karploomi toodetakse, on esinenud uut merelist toksiini Amnesic Shellfish Poisoning (ASP), mis v&otilde;ib ohustada tarbija tervist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the public health requirements concerning live bivalve molluscs in Chapter V of the Annex to Directive 91/492/EEC must be adjusted to take account of this new marine toxin; </inglise>
<eesti> nimetatud uue merelise toksiini arvessev&otilde;tmiseks tuleb kohandada direktiivi 91/942/EM&Uuml; lisa V peat&uuml;ki tervishoiun&otilde;udeid, mis k&auml;sitlevad elusaid kahepoolmelisi karploomi; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas an acceptable limit value must be set for this new marine toxin, in order to protect public health; </inglise>
<eesti> rahva tervise kaitseks tuleb ette n&auml;ha nimetatud uue merelise toksiini lubatav piirnorm; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas experience has shown that the registration document for the identification of the batches of molluscs provided for in point 6 of Chapter II of the Annex to Directive 91/492/EEC should contain information concerning the health status of the area of origin and any purification or relaying operations that have been carried out on the molluscs; </inglise>
<eesti> kogemused on n&auml;idanud, et direktiivi 91/492/EM&Uuml; lisa II peat&uuml;ki punktis 6 s&auml;testatud registreerimisdokument elusate kahepoolmeliste karploomade partiide identifitseerimiseks peaks sisaldama teavet esialgse kogumisala sanitaarseisundi ning k&otilde;ikide karploomadele tehtud puhastamiste v&otilde;i &uuml;lekandmiste kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it must be possible to trace the origin of bivalve molluscs placed on the market; whereas to do this it should be possible to link the information shown on the registration document with each batch placed on the market in a register kept by the dispatch centre; </inglise>
<eesti> turuleviidud kahepoolmeliste karploomade p&auml;ritolu peab olema v&otilde;imalik v&auml;lja selgitada; seet&otilde;ttu peaks olema v&otilde;imalik siduda registreerimisdokumendis esitatud teavet iga turuleviidud partiiga v&auml;ljastuskeskuses peetavas arvestusraamatus; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas a standard registration document would be more easily understood by operators and inspection services regardless of the language in which it is drawn up; whereas such standard document should be introduced by the Commission, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;itajatele ja j&auml;relevalvetalitustele oleks kergemini m&otilde;istetavam registreerimisdokumendi t&uuml;&uuml;pvorm, s&otilde;ltumata keelest, milles see on koostatud; komisjon peaks sellise dokumendivormi kehtestama, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS DIRECTIVE: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA DIREKTIIVI. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> The Annex to Directive 91/492/EEC is hereby amended as follows: </inglise>
<eesti> Direktiivi 91/492/EM&Uuml; lisa muudetakse j&auml;rgmiselt. </eesti>
<inglise> 1. point 6 of Chapter II shall be replaced by the following: </inglise>
<eesti> 1. II peat&uuml;ki punkt 6 asendatakse j&auml;rgmisega: </eesti>
<inglise> '6. </inglise>
<eesti> "6. </eesti>
<inglise> A registration document for the identification of batches of live bivalve molluscs during transport from the production area to a dispatch centre, purification centre, relaying area or processing plant must be issued by the competent authority upon request by the gatherer. </inglise>
<eesti> P&auml;dev asutus peab tootja n&otilde;udmisel v&auml;lja andma registreerimisdokumendi elusate kahepoolmeliste karploomade partiide identifitseerimiseks tootmisalalt v&auml;ljastuskeskusesse, puhastuskeskusesse, &uuml;lekandealale v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tlemisettev&otilde;ttesse vedamise ajal. </eesti>
<inglise> For each batch, the gatherer must complete legibly and indelibly the relevant sections of the registration document which must contain the following information: - the gatherer's identity and address, </inglise>
<eesti> Iga partii puhul peab tootja loetavalt ja kustumatute t&auml;htedega t&auml;itma asjakohased lahtrid registreerimisdokumendis, mis peab sisaldama j&auml;rgmist teavet: </eesti>
<inglise> - the date of harvesting, - the location of the production area described in as precise detail as is practicable or by a code number, </inglise>
<eesti> - tootja andmed ja asukoht, </eesti>
<inglise> - the health status of the production area as referred to in Chapter I, - the shellfish species and quantity indicated in as precise detail as is practicable, </inglise>
<eesti> - kogumise kuup&auml;ev, </eesti>
<inglise> - the approval number and place of destination for wrapping, relaying, purification or processing. The registration document must be dated and signed by the gatherer. </inglise>
<eesti> - tootmisala asukoha v&otilde;imalikult t&auml;psed andmed v&otilde;i koodnumber, </eesti>
<inglise> 2. point 9 of Chapter III shall be replaced by the following: </inglise>
<eesti> - karpide liigi ja koguse v&otilde;imalikult t&auml;psed andmed, </eesti>
<inglise> 3. the second subparagraph of point 13 of section III of Chapter IV shall be replaced by the following: </inglise>

<eesti> Registreerimisdokumendid tuleb nummerdada. </eesti>
<inglise> 'Purification centres dispatching batches of live bivalve molluscs to dispatch centres must provide a registration document, a specimen of which will be drawn up by the Commission in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 12 of the Directive, setting out, in addition to the information specified in point 6 of Chapter II of this Annex, inter alia the approval number and address of the purification plant and the duration of purification, the dates of entering and leaving the purification centre, together with any other information needed to identify and trace the product. </inglise>
<eesti> P&auml;dev asutus peab pidama registrit, kuhu on m&auml;rgitud registreerimisdokumentide numbrid ja elusaid kahepoolmelisi karploomi koguvate isikute nimed, kellele need dokumendid on v&auml;lja antud. Elusate kahepoolmeliste karploomade iga partii registreerimisdokument tuleb partii edasisaatmisel v&auml;ljastuskeskusesse, puhastuskeskusesse, &uuml;lekandealale v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tlemisettev&otilde;ttesse kalendertempliga m&auml;rgistada ning nimetatud keskuste, alade v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tete k&auml;itajad peavad seda dokumenti s&auml;ilitama v&auml;hemalt 12 kuu jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise> ' ; 4. point 4 of section IV of Chapter IV shall be replaced by the following: </inglise>
<eesti> Lisaks on ka tootja kohustatud registreerimisdokumenti sama ajavahemiku jooksul alles hoidma. </eesti>
<inglise> - dispatch details including the names and addresses of consignees, the dates and quantities of live bivalve molluscs dispatched, together with the corresponding entry registration document number(s). </inglise>
<eesti> Kui kogumist teostavad samad isikud, kes t&ouml;&ouml;tavad sihtkoha v&auml;ljastuskeskuses, puhastuskeskuses, &uuml;lekandealal v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tlemisettev&otilde;ttes, v&otilde;ib registreerimisdokumendi asendada alalise transpordiloaga, mille annab p&auml;dev asutus. </eesti>
<inglise> These data must be classified chronologically and preserved for a period to be laid down by the competent authority, but not less than twelve months. ' ; </inglise>
<eesti> Direktiivi artiklis 12 s&auml;testatud korras kehtestab komisjon registreerimisdokumendi t&uuml;&uuml;pvormi, mis sisaldab viidet mitmetele sinna lisatavatele n&otilde;uetele, mida nimetatakse k&auml;esoleva lisa II, III ja IV peat&uuml;kis." </eesti>
